  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="1118775">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1118775/" class="title-link">换一个角度看历史，还历史本来面目</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1118775"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/1012705/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1012705-1.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/1012705/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">scott</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2007-02-01"
      class="main-meta">2007-02-01 23:37:10</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1118775_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  很好的一本书，给出了很多历史的细节，探寻了那些被湮没被篡改或者被扭曲的人和事。他们不该被遗忘，他们对我们这个国家既有贡献也有过错甚至罪孽。人非圣贤，孰能无过。评价历史人物应该功过分明吧。

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
